The following are some of the books that can help you in understanding and learning big-data:-

### Big Data Books

1. Big Data For Dummies
This book is written by Judith Hurwitz, Alan, Fern Halper and Marcia Kaufman. This book gives a clear overview as to what is big data and
is useful for beginners who have just started big data.
- [Amazon](https://www.amazon.com/Big-Data-Dummies-Judith-Hurwitz/dp/1118504224)
- ISBN-10: 9781118504222
- ISBN-13: 978-1118504222

2. Too Big to Ignore: The Business Case for Big Data
The book written by Phil Simon explains how big data is not only an area of potential innovation but also a crucial factor that companies
must address to survive in a modern workplace. This book can be seen as a great introduction to big data.
- [Amazon](https://www.amazon.com/Too-Big-Ignore-Business-Wiley/dp/1119217849)
- ISBN-10: 1119217849
- ISBN-13: 978-1119217849

3. The Human Face of Big Data
This book which is written by Rick Smolan is defining Big Data and its application in various fields like academics and healthcare.
- [Amazon](https://www.amazon.in/Human-Face-Big-Data/dp/1454908270/)
- ISBN-10: 1454908270
- ISBN-13: 978-1454908270

4. Big Data in Practice: How 45 Successful Companies Used Big Data Analytics to Deliver Extraordinary Results
This book written by Bernard Marr gives an insight as to how the companies that are listed profiled the data, what data was used and what 
problems were solved with this.
- [Amazon](https://www.amazon.com/Big-Data-Practice-Successful-Extraordinary/dp/1119231388)
- ISBN-10: 1119231388
- ISBN-13: 978-1119231388
